title: Data Scraper for Instagram Using Proxy Server
jobs_text:
"1. Create a script to scrap all the details of the influencer based on their user handle. title: Simple Scrapers Needed - Continuous
jobs_text:
"Hello, 
 
We're looking at individual scrapers for about 73 different listing/directory type sites. (Think Yellow Pages - but only simpler).  
 
Each scraper should be able to do the following  
 
1. We're able to provide an input file. For example, with Category + City list preferably in a CSV and the scraper runs through all listings of the city in each category. 
2. The scraper uses proxies (You can tell us your preferred provider + format) 
3. The scraper outputs the requested fields 
4. The scraper handles pagination & errors (when a category is empty etc.) 
5. The output is saved to one single CSV file.  
 
We will require 73 different scrapers, as the inputs for each will be different. (Some are government sites, some are data sites, etc.) 
 
We don't need a GUI - we're capable of running python scripts. We will provide you with the site URL + fields that need to be scraped 
 
You would be required to write a test scraper script for one site. We'll analyze the code to see how optimized it is. If it works and runs relatively bug-free we will hand over the rest of the scraping job to you.  
 
Please provide us with a ballpark code for every script/scraper - and for the 73 together.  
 
This is python only. We're not interested in Chrome-based scraping, Imacros, or any other scraping program. 
 
Thanks"

title: Build a comparison tool
jobs_text:
"Parts of this job may require database and indexing skillset.   
View the Comparison Tool 2022 file to see more details about this job. 
 
This job will be broken up into 3 milestones.   
 
Milestone 1: $50 
Write code that edits excel files and reprints the data on 2 new tabs in a vertical format instead of the horizontal way it is now. 
 
Milestone 2: $200 to $250 
Create an app/program that finds all the outputs that are within proximity of each other and present them in a bucketed manner. 
 
Milestone 3: $250 to $450 
Add functionality to the program created in milestone 2.  
Make custom searches available.   
 
I use Excel to manually perform my searches.  You can use whatever you determine is best for this job.   
I need all three milestones complete before Wednesday, February 2nd.  If this work is beyond your skillset and/or you can't complete it by then, please don't apply.   
 
Those who want to be considered for Milestones 2 and 3 need to download the updated Tester File(s) and look at how I perform milestone 3 manually on the results sheet.  This is the process I need automated.  Example 3 is critical in understanding my process.  
Show your competency by creating a report for time block 61, making buckets between 23.270 and 23.320 for group 1 only..  This is a very small area of the potential full range.  Provide what you think buckets should look like for milestone 2 and 3 for the range I just mentioned.  Use a proximity of 0.003 for when a mandatory time is found.  
Send me your results and I'll check to see if you got the right answers.  If you do, then I know I can give you the job. 
 
Here's an overview of the Grid file your program will be working with.   
Typically, Gird files come with about 3.6 Million outputs spread out over 300 Time Blocks.  Each Time Block has about 12,000 outputs.  Each group in a Time Block has about 4,000 outputs. So when your program searches one time block, it searches each group for matches, potentially searching up to 4,000 outputs at a time.    
When the request is to search 3 times block at once, for example, your program would be comparing 12,000 outputs per group.  "

title: Product Page Scraping Bot
jobs_text:
"Our product Trolli is a Chrome extension shopping basket. When a Trolli user is (signed in and Trolli is active) is on a product page Trolli will manually scrape relevant information from the page (The product price etc) and will display this on our widget, giving the user the option to save this item (and the info) in their basket. 
We would like the automate this process, as well as automatically adding new websites to be scraped, as a user visits a new website. 
Objective: 
To scrape from a webpage - Webpage URL, Website name, Product title, Product Image, Product 
Price. 
 
Currently: 
We have a JSON file websites' with a dictionary of websites. 
We manually inspect each webpage and take the classname (and for some cases - for the image the child element) for each relevant div. 
These classnames are manually added to our JSON file which is then called when we run our extension. 
 
url: 'aliexpress.com' 
website: 'aliexpress' 
titleSelectors: ['.product-title'], 
imageSelectors: ['.image-view-magnifier-wrap img'], 
priceSelectors: ['.uniform-banner-box-price'], 
 
On each webpage we run our JS and loop through the 'websites' urls until we have a match with the current location.href 
When we have a match we have a function to getTextElement or getlmageElement by using the 'websites' selectors to querySelector the relevant information. 
 
What we want: 
When Trolli is active and a user is on any web page: 
- To recognise a product page (looking for relevant info - price etc) 
- Automatically scrape the ÜRL, website name (usually from URL), title, image and price from page. 
JSON file to be automatically updated when a previously unknown website is added with the info (above.) 
(We will then integrate this into our function for displaying and saving the info) 
(An automated testing/QA system)"

title: Web scraping, GUI design and big data analysis with Python
jobs_text:
"Hi, 
 
I am looking for a Python developer who is experienced in web scraping (using Scrapy module), big data analysis, and have a fair UI/UX design experience.  
 
You are required to crawl data from a specified target website (e.g. Amazon or TripAdvisor, or other if you are familiar with them, but Amazon is preferred) and visualize the data in a graphic user interface GUI. The data is then analyzed by the big data techniques (NLP is preferred, other is also acceptable if you can prove the complexity) 
 
Since I don’t specific too many details at the moment, you can introduce some idea if you can achieve it. Here is some of my suggestion. If NLP is used, you may determine if the comment is consistent to the grading. If clustering is used, you may determine if there is any anomaly user. It is important to show the the outcome of the techniques used is meaningful. 
 
In short, what you need to do is: 
(1)	Crawl the data from a target website and store it in a database 
(2)	Design a GUI and visualize the data retrieved from the database 
(3)	Apply big data techniques to the data 
 
For the first two, I will give  5-7 days to complete since it is not really difficult if you have such experience. For the third one, I believe it is sufficient to be done in 10 to 15 days, but more can be given if I believe it turns out to be good work after reviewing. 
 
It is expected the developer should have good communication to me and, as we may discuss many times during the development and also I can keep on track your progress. 
 
I will pay more if you did a great job."
questions_list: [' Describe your recent experience with similar projects ']

title: Help us build web scrapers
jobs_text:
"👋 Hi Freelancers, 
 
We have an exciting problem: scraping 5,000 - 7,000 rental agent websites in the Netherlands. 
 
To do this we've built a tool that allows you to rapidly create web scrapers. The tool is a Google Chrome Extension that you can install in your browser. Then, using a JSON configuration file you can rapidly build web scrapers. 
 
We're looking for people who are able to use this tool to build web scrapers for these rental agent websites. Preferably we would like to work long-term with someone, as getting to know the ins and outs of the tool might take a bit of work. 
 
As a try-out, we want to start with 5 hours of work, and if we're happy with the quality we can make a longer arrangement. 
 
Each rental agent website is slightly different, so we're looking for someone who is able to be creative and find solutions for each rental agent website. Being able to work precisely is a requirement as the data needs to be scraped exactly as it is stated on the website. 
 
Knowledge of the Dutch language is NOT required as our tool works great with Google Translate. 
 
Skills required: 
 - JSON 
 - HTML and CSS selectors. 
 - Regex (regular expressions). 
 
To get a better idea of how the tool works.

title: Scraping of websites using Zyte/Scrapy
jobs_text:
"We are looking for help to scrape daily listings of three (3) marketplace websites, specifically pet section and then pushing that scraped data into a database. If project is successful, we have many more sites to scrape. 
 
Ideally the data is pushed to our BigQuery data warehouse, where every website has its own table. If that doesn't work we have a postgres database we could push data to. 
 
The websites to scrape are the following: 
 
- Gumtree.co.uk 
- Preloved.co.uk 
- Freeads.co.uk 
 
Please see attached guide to scraping the sites with URLs included and what data should be collected. Points for a successful project include: 
 
Technical details 
- Well-documented code 
- Only unique listings should be pushed (based on ad id) - if entry exists, entry should be updated 
- Data pushed to Google bigquery  (optionally postgresql) 
- Crawler to run every 6 hours to check if new results have been published on the website 
- Please use Scrapy, where we use Zyte to manage all crawlers. Access to our Zyte account will be provided 
- Push all crawler scripts to our git repository (access will be given) 
 
Please get in touch if you have any questions! 
 
 
/Emil"

title: Twitter / instagram api extraction expert
jobs_text:
"We need the following doing - You MUST have worked with large scale scraping and twitter APIs 
 
Twitter Scraper - (probably best using API with multiple accounts) -  
 
1. start with a list of twitter profiles (50k) + new accounts will be added daily I will provide. 
2. visit each instagram account daily and take followers number, following number, bio, if verified, date created, profile image, number of tweets, date of last tweet, likes, + comments + retweet number of the last tweet, name, @ 
3. Scrape all followers data from 2. And take - followers number, following number, bio, if verified, date created, profile image, number of tweets, date of last tweet, likes, + comments + retweet number of the last tweet, name, @ 
4. Repeat 2. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile) 
5. Repeat 3. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile) 
6. Take each of the 50k + new accounts will be added daily, account names @ and query twitter to see number of @ mentions / tagged and date / time of each 
7. Repeat 6. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile) 
 
 
 
Instagram Scraper - (I think will need to be scraped as won’t get API access) - 
 
1. start with a list of instagram profiles (50k) + new accounts will be added daily I will provide. 
2. visit each instagram profile daily and take followers number, following number, bio, if verified, date created, profile image, number of posts, date of last post, likes, + comments of the last post, name, @ 
3. Scrape all followers data from 2. And take followers number, following number, bio, if verified, date created, profile image, number of posts, date of last post, likes, + comments of the last post, name, @ 
4. Repeat 2. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile). 
5. Repeat 3. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile) 
6. Take each of the 50k + new accounts will be added daily, account names @ and query instagram to see number of @ mentions / tagged and date / time of each 
7. Repeat 6. Daily (at similar time each day for a profile) 
 
 
this is long term work required daily data we need sending to our server  
 
work to start asap - $600 a month"

title: Need a python scripts that scans webpage and sends mail
jobs_text:
"We need a python script that scans the following page:  
 
 
Script must scan the page with an x second interval that we set as variable in the code. 
 
The script must scan the code for occurrences of the string "0000,#" where the value of # should be set as a variable in the code, so if we set #=2 it should scan for "0000,2" 
 
We should be able to set a list of numbers for "SectionName" that the script does not search. Hence if we set ExcludeSections=[1,2,3,4] the script should search all sections but that one.

Where x, # and url are variables that we can set in the code. The mail should be sent with the attached Mailgun code."

title: Software Engineer (Web Scraping)
jobs_text:
"We are looking for an experienced Python developer with practical experience writing, deploying, and managing web scrapers. The successful candidate will be responsible for both design, maintenance, and ensuring successful onboarding.  
 
We are a small, remote team of technically savvy and friendly developers with a focus on quality and consistent improvement. We develop regulatory technology services for businesses such as banks and cybersecurity firms, and our clients include some household names. 
 
Our ordinary data sources are HTML, XML, and RSS feeds in the public domain: legislation, regulation, news, and enforcement information. We currently have ~150 spiders running in production and are continuously adding more.  
 
The successful candidate will be an efficient, driven worker who is able to follow well-defined processes for preparing documents for enrichment and pushing to the S3 Amazon platform, where it will be picked and processed up by our backend. They should also be an independent thinker who is able to speak up and start discussions where they believe the process can be improved.  
 
We believe in maximum automation and excellent software design. We believe in merit and encourage all candidates who fit the requirements to apply. Developers who demonstrate strong abilities can over time expect plenty of opportunity to learn about new areas of software development outside of their core specialisation and are encouraged to spend time engaging in research and development. 
 
 
Requirements:  
•	Solid understanding of Python as a language 
•	Working knowledge of relational databases and SQL 
•	Driven to write consistently clean, DRY, and maintainable code.  
•	Familiarity with scraping and parsing frameworks like Scrapy and BeautifulSoup, along with JSON parsing and validation via schemas 
•	Experience writing involved test cases to prove that data extraction works as specified 
•	Experience working with at least one cloud platform, preferably AWS. 
•	A team player in a fast-paced work environment 
 
 
Nice to have:  
•	Experience with AWS (S3 buckets and queues) 
•	Experience of deploying to Zyte (formerly ScrapingHub) 
•	An exposure to and understanding of REST APIs"

title: Scrape Twitter looking for a certain URL
jobs_text:
"I need an app created to do the following. 
 
1. Continually spider and scrape Twitter for any posts containing any URL's from premint.xyz 
 
2. Save the premint.xyz URL, twitter username that posted the link, and time of twitter post to a database and/or google sheet.  Make sure to only display the core premint.xyz/projectname url.  For instance many times a URL may look like    I would ONLY want the   part recorded into the database/google sheet. 
 
3. Visit the premint.xyz link that was found and scrape the "Registration Closes", "Number of Winners", "Official link", H1, and Discord & Twitter links (if they exist) to the database and/or google sheet.  It needs to have the ability to switch between using a google sheet and or a database with a front end accessible through a web browser. 
 
4. List all of the data for each Twitter post/premint.xyz into the same row in a google sheet and/or web page that is sorted by date of twitter post on default but can also be sorted by any of the columns. 
 
5.  Have the option to filter results on the front end depending on each column.  For instance, if I wanted to search for a certain twitter username and see all of the posts they had with different premint.xyz URL's. 
 
6. Check to make sure NO duplicate premint.xyz URL's are added to the database. 
 
7. Ability to send email notification as soon as a new premint.xyz URL is found with all of the information collected also sent in the email.  I will also need the ability to turn email notifications on or off. 
 
8. I will need well commented code and Instructions on how to set everything up. 
 
 
IMPORTANT: When applying MAKE SURE to give a quick overview of which languages/technology's you would be using to accomplish the project along with a timeframe on how long you estimate it will take to complete."
